-- French court of appeal upholds Kerviel conviction
-- By Chine Labbe
-- Wed Mar 19, 2014 09:16AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, March 19 (Reuters) - France's highest court of appeal upheld former Societe Generale <SOGN.PA> trader Jerome Kerviel's criminal conviction and three-year jail sentence over massive market bets that brought the French bank to the brink of collapse in 2008.

